WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.080 --> 00:00:02.675
<i>Previously on
"The Vampire Diaries..."</i>

2
00:00:02.720 --> 00:00:04.530
<i>The only thing stronger
than your craving</i>

3
00:00:04.536 --> 00:00:06.591
<i>for blood is your love
for this one girl.</i>

4
00:00:06.615 --> 00:00:09.205
Your humanity is killing you.

5
00:00:09.618 --> 00:00:11.318
Turn it off!

6
00:00:11.343 --> 00:00:13.061
- What did you do?
- I fixed him.

7
00:00:13.065 --> 00:00:15.705
Fight for it. Feel something.
Anything. Stefan.

8
00:00:15.775 --> 00:00:17.560
'Cause if you don't. you're
going to lose me forever.

9
00:00:17.573 --> 00:00:20.903
I've heard about you.
Crazy. impulsive vampire.

10
00:00:20.993 --> 00:00:22.523
<i>In love with
his brother's girl.</i>

11
00:00:22.535 --> 00:00:25.325
As long as Klaus is alive.
I do what he says.

12
00:00:31.703 --> 00:00:33.548
What the hell did you do?

13
00:00:33.565 --> 00:00:34.935
He's earned his freedom.

14
00:00:35.043 --> 00:00:37.188
I had Klaus. This could
have all been over.

15
00:00:37.203 --> 00:00:38.553
We'll survive this.

16
00:00:38.643 --> 00:00:40.513
We're never getting
Stefan back.

17
00:00:40.563 --> 00:00:42.648
Then we'll let him go.

18
00:00:42.658 --> 00:00:45.103
- What now?
- Now. I reunite my family.

19
00:00:45.113 --> 00:00:47.758
You mean. the people you
cart around in caskets.

20
00:00:47.808 --> 00:00:49.370
What's the matter. Klaus

21
00:00:49.378 --> 00:00:52.718
I will kill you and everyone
you've ever met.

22
00:00:52.798 --> 00:00:55.418
Do that. and you will never
see your family again.

23
00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:03.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

24
00:04:16.288 --> 00:04:19.588
Excuse me.

25
00:04:19.668 --> 00:04:21.858
I should have been watching
where I was going.

26
00:04:22.838 --> 00:04:24.948
Don't worry about it.

27
00:04:25.143 --> 00:04:27.358
You have a nice day.

28
00:04:31.098 --> 00:04:32.378
I think I'm going crazy.

29
00:04:32.438 --> 00:04:34.918
I'm totally paranoid
all the time.

30
00:04:34.968 --> 00:04:36.718
You have a right to be.

31
00:04:36.758 --> 00:04:39.163
Klaus is sill out there. and he knows
you tried to kill him.

32
00:04:39.188 --> 00:04:40.380
Why hasn't he made a move?

33
00:04:40.388 --> 00:04:43.278
There's been no sign
of him. nothing.

34
00:04:43.458 --> 00:04:45.863
Just my slow spiral
into insanity.

35
00:04:45.948 --> 00:04:47.710
Join the club.

36
00:04:47.728 --> 00:04:49.718
Every time I close my eyes.

37
00:04:49.768 --> 00:04:52.398
I have that nightmare
on repeat.

38
00:04:52.488 --> 00:04:53.688
- The same dream?
- Yeah.

39
00:04:53.738 --> 00:04:57.358
4 coffins. Klaus is in one of them.
It's weird.

40
00:04:57.408 --> 00:05:00.198
What if it's not
just... Some dream?

41
00:05:00.248 --> 00:05:03.498
What if it's. like. you know.
a witch dream?

42
00:05:03.568 --> 00:05:06.588
It's just stress.

43
00:05:06.668 --> 00:05:09.418
What about Stefan

44
00:05:10.918 --> 00:05:13.928
he betrayed us. Bonnie.

45
00:05:14.008 --> 00:05:16.078
The Stefan
that we know is gone.

46
00:05:16.128 --> 00:05:18.708
How is Damon handling that?

47
00:05:18.768 --> 00:05:21.778
Damon is...

48
00:05:21.848 --> 00:05:22.968
Damon.

49
00:05:23.048 --> 00:05:25.088
Uh. you have your choice...

50
00:05:25.138 --> 00:05:27.588
Bloody Mary. screwdriver.

51
00:05:27.638 --> 00:05:29.778
Brunch in a bottle.

52
00:05:32.358 --> 00:05:34.028
Come on. Ric.

53
00:05:34.098 --> 00:05:35.528
I can't drink
all this by myself.

54
00:05:35.598 --> 00:05:37.818
I mean. I can. but then.

55
00:05:37.898 --> 00:05:40.648
Somebody's getting naked.

56
00:05:41.768 --> 00:05:43.458
Oh. man.

57
00:05:43.538 --> 00:05:45.658
I can't believe you're
making me drink alone.

58
00:05:45.738 --> 00:05:47.328
I'm busy.

59
00:05:47.408 --> 00:05:49.378
It's the eve of Klausageddon.

60
00:05:49.448 --> 00:05:50.778
You're doing homework?

61
00:05:50.828 --> 00:05:52.048
This may come as a shock.

62
00:05:52.118 --> 00:05:54.798
but I am not here
to hang out with you.

63
00:05:54.878 --> 00:05:59.558
I'm here to see Jeremy. who is
an hour late for his shift.

64
00:05:59.618 --> 00:06:02.468
Kids today.
Where are their values?

65
00:06:04.388 --> 00:06:05.758
That's his midterm paper.

66
00:06:05.808 --> 00:06:07.558
Copied it straight
off the internet.

67
00:06:07.628 --> 00:06:08.848
Didn't even try to hide it.

68
00:06:08.928 --> 00:06:10.848
Ooh. Somebody's
getting grounded.

69
00:06:10.928 --> 00:06:12.018
Did you say you were
waiting for Jeremy...

70
00:06:12.098 --> 00:06:13.968
As in Jeremy Gilbert?

71
00:06:14.018 --> 00:06:16.968
Yeah. He was fired last week.

72
00:06:18.488 --> 00:06:19.778
Oops.

73
00:06:25.448 --> 00:06:27.778
Nice shot.

74
00:06:27.828 --> 00:06:29.328
So what's the point
of this. again?

75
00:06:29.418 --> 00:06:31.368
The point is I'm
pissed at Caroline.

76
00:06:31.448 --> 00:06:33.008
and Bonnie dumped your ass.

77
00:06:33.088 --> 00:06:36.078
The point...

78
00:06:36.138 --> 00:06:38.488
Is to get drunk
and shoot stuff.

79
00:06:38.548 --> 00:06:40.758
Profound.

80
00:06:40.828 --> 00:06:41.998
Alaric finds out I took this.

81
00:06:42.048 --> 00:06:45.048
he's going to use it on me.

82
00:06:45.138 --> 00:06:47.598
So. what's the deal with that?

83
00:06:47.668 --> 00:06:49.338
He's. like. your guardian now?

84
00:06:49.388 --> 00:06:53.178
Sort of. yeah.
I think he feels responsible for us.

85
00:06:53.228 --> 00:06:55.008
You like him?

86
00:06:55.058 --> 00:06:57.478
Yeah. Yeah. I like him.

87
00:06:57.528 --> 00:06:59.828
Hey. you want to move
out of the way?

88
00:06:59.898 --> 00:07:03.498
I'm a hybrid. Gilbert.

89
00:07:03.568 --> 00:07:07.018
You can't kill me unless you cut
off my head or rip out my heart.

90
00:07:07.068 --> 00:07:11.028
And you're not going to do it
with that lame-ass crossbow.

91
00:07:11.078 --> 00:07:12.358
Go ahead.

92
00:07:12.408 --> 00:07:14.798
Take a shot.

93
00:07:14.858 --> 00:07:17.078
Unless you don't think
you can hit me.

94
00:07:30.058 --> 00:07:33.978
Jeremy. the minute that
you get this. call me.

95
00:07:35.768 --> 00:07:37.348
You're feisty when you're mad.

96
00:07:37.398 --> 00:07:40.218
It's not that I'm mad.
I'm just... I'm worried.

97
00:07:40.268 --> 00:07:43.028
Why

98
00:07:43.078 --> 00:07:44.528
I think he'll survive. Elena.

99
00:07:44.578 --> 00:07:46.198
He's spiraling.

100
00:07:46.248 --> 00:07:49.358
Ever since Bonnie broke up
with him. he's moody.

101
00:07:49.418 --> 00:07:51.728
He's not really
talking to anyone.

102
00:07:51.788 --> 00:07:53.198
Just a typical teenager.

103
00:07:53.248 --> 00:07:56.908
Who's seeing ghosts and who's lost
everyone that he cares about.

104
00:07:56.958 --> 00:08:00.708
Not everyone. He still has you.

105
00:08:05.518 --> 00:08:06.718
You ok?

106
00:08:06.768 --> 00:08:08.878
What makes you think
I'm not ok?

107
00:08:08.938 --> 00:08:10.918
Well. you're a day drunk.

108
00:08:10.968 --> 00:08:12.938
It's not exactly
your most attractive look.

109
00:08:13.018 --> 00:08:16.388
Oh. What is my most
attractive look?

110
00:08:16.438 --> 00:08:17.808
Uh-uh.

111
00:08:17.888 --> 00:08:19.928
I'm not saying you have
any attractive look.

112
00:08:19.978 --> 00:08:21.308
I'm just...

113
00:08:21.398 --> 00:08:24.898
Saying this is
my least favorite one.

114
00:08:24.948 --> 00:08:28.868
Noted. See if I can
make any improvements.

115
00:08:28.938 --> 00:08:31.738
Don't mind me.

116
00:08:31.788 --> 00:08:33.128
Oh.

117
00:08:34.108 --> 00:08:36.248
You going to do this
in the grill.

118
00:08:36.298 --> 00:08:37.548
in front of everyone?

119
00:08:37.608 --> 00:08:38.958
It's a little beneath
you. don't you think?

120
00:08:39.048 --> 00:08:40.568
I don't know
what you're talking about.

121
00:08:40.618 --> 00:08:41.898
I just came down
to my local pub.

122
00:08:41.918 --> 00:08:43.168
To grab a drink with a mate.

123
00:08:43.248 --> 00:08:46.718
Get a round. then.
would you. Tony?

124
00:08:51.128 --> 00:08:52.808
I'm surprised
you stuck around town.

125
00:08:52.898 --> 00:08:54.148
Long enough for happy hour.

126
00:08:54.228 --> 00:08:56.798
My sister seems to be missing.
Need to sort that out.

127
00:08:56.848 --> 00:08:59.428
Cute. blonde bombshell

128
00:08:59.488 --> 00:09:01.488
shouldn't be too hard to find.

129
00:09:01.568 --> 00:09:03.518
Truth is.

130
00:09:03.608 --> 00:09:06.278
I've grown to rather like
your little town.

131
00:09:06.328 --> 00:09:09.608
Thinking I might fancy
a home here.

132
00:09:09.658 --> 00:09:13.278
I imagine you're wondering
how does this affect you.

133
00:09:13.328 --> 00:09:15.998
And the answer is.
not in the slightest.

134
00:09:16.088 --> 00:09:17.748
As long as I get what I want.
and everyone behaves themselves.

135
00:09:17.818 --> 00:09:20.258
you can go on living your little
lives however you choose.

136
00:09:21.758 --> 00:09:22.988
You have my word.

137
00:09:23.038 --> 00:09:25.588
What more could
you possibly want?

138
00:09:25.658 --> 00:09:26.928
Well. for starters.

139
00:09:26.998 --> 00:09:28.638
you can tell me where
I might find Stefan.

140
00:09:28.678 --> 00:09:31.378
Stefan skipped town the second
he saved your ass.

141
00:09:31.655 --> 00:09:34.205
Well. you see. that is a shame.

142
00:09:35.688 --> 00:09:38.273
Your brother stole from me.

143
00:09:38.277 --> 00:09:41.197
I need him found so I can
take back what's mine.

144
00:09:41.438 --> 00:09:44.278
That sounds like a Klaus
and Stefan problem.

145
00:09:51.048 --> 00:09:54.068
Well. this is me broadening
the scope. sweetheart.

146
00:11:05.158 --> 00:11:07.108
Hello. Bonnie.

147
00:11:08.298 --> 00:11:09.848
Stefan.

148
00:11:14.998 --> 00:11:17.723
- You followed me here?
- Yeah.

149
00:11:17.958 --> 00:11:19.973
It wasn't too hard.

150
00:11:20.008 --> 00:11:21.853
You should probably be
more careful.

151
00:11:21.905 --> 00:11:23.295
What do you want with me?

152
00:11:23.320 --> 00:11:25.120
Relax. I just need your help.

153
00:11:25.250 --> 00:11:26.470
Why would I help you?

154
00:11:26.540 --> 00:11:28.870
Elena said you saved
Klaus's life.

155
00:11:28.960 --> 00:11:31.710
Let me fill you in on a
little secret about Klaus.

156
00:11:31.790 --> 00:11:33.540
He kept his family
with him at all times.

157
00:11:33.630 --> 00:11:36.210
Daggered. stored in coffins.

158
00:11:36.300 --> 00:11:38.330
And now. I have them.

159
00:11:38.380 --> 00:11:41.250
And I need you to help
keep them hidden.

160
00:11:41.320 --> 00:11:43.970
You're out of your mind.
You're just going to make him angrier.

161
00:11:44.020 --> 00:11:45.300
His family is his one weakness.

162
00:11:45.360 --> 00:11:47.560
As long as I have that.
I can ruin him.

163
00:11:47.640 --> 00:11:50.890
I don't have enough power
to hide 4 Originals.

164
00:11:50.980 --> 00:11:53.480
You're a witch. You hate Klaus.

165
00:11:53.530 --> 00:11:55.450
I know you can figure
something out.

166
00:11:57.900 --> 00:11:59.190
You ready?

167
00:11:59.250 --> 00:12:01.520
Vampires. hybrids.
and Originals.

168
00:12:01.570 --> 00:12:03.410
No problem.

169
00:12:03.470 --> 00:12:06.080
My rebellious brother...
I'm worried.

170
00:12:06.160 --> 00:12:08.580
Proof you're still human.

171
00:12:10.660 --> 00:12:13.200
Just in time.
We're cooking.

172
00:12:13.250 --> 00:12:14.670
Sorry.
Just passing through.

173
00:12:14.720 --> 00:12:17.550
Aww. Well. I thought
we'd all stay in.

174
00:12:17.620 --> 00:12:21.220
Have a meal together like
a typical atypical family.

175
00:12:21.310 --> 00:12:22.830
- Why?
- Maybe because you got fired.

176
00:12:22.890 --> 00:12:24.710
And you didn't tell anyone.

177
00:12:26.650 --> 00:12:28.510
Look. can we do this later?

178
00:12:28.570 --> 00:12:30.880
I made plans with Tyler.
He's right outside.

179
00:12:30.930 --> 00:12:32.690
Wait.

180
00:12:33.240 --> 00:12:34.770
When did you start hanging
out with Tyler Rockwell?

181
00:12:34.850 --> 00:12:37.510
I don't know. Does it matter?

182
00:12:37.570 --> 00:12:39.690
Yeah. Jeremy. it matters.

183
00:12:39.740 --> 00:12:42.160
He was sired by Klaus.
He's dangerous.

184
00:12:42.230 --> 00:12:44.710
He can still hear you.
He's right outside.

185
00:12:44.780 --> 00:12:46.570
Besides. you of all people
are going to lecture me.

186
00:12:46.620 --> 00:12:47.900
On who I can and can't
hang out with?

187
00:12:47.950 --> 00:12:49.000
What is with the attitude?

188
00:12:49.070 --> 00:12:51.790
Whatever. This is lame.
Tyler's waiting.

189
00:12:51.870 --> 00:12:55.040
No. Oh. no. no.
You're not going anywhere.

190
00:12:55.090 --> 00:12:57.340
especially not with Tyler.

191
00:12:57.410 --> 00:13:00.210
I'm with her on this. Jer.
Sorry.

192
00:13:01.930 --> 00:13:03.420
All right. Fine.
You want me to stay in?

193
00:13:03.470 --> 00:13:05.311
Let's all stay in. then.
Yo. Tyler. come on in.

194
00:13:05.390 --> 00:13:06.720
Jeremy...

195
00:13:17.530 --> 00:13:19.930
I think it's about time
we had a drink. don't you?

196
00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:22.070
I'd say we're overdue.

197
00:13:22.120 --> 00:13:24.450
Well. you've been so busy. what with
all your plotting and scheming.

198
00:13:24.540 --> 00:13:27.410
You know me... Never miss a chance
to plan an epic failure.

199
00:13:27.460 --> 00:13:29.290
Don't be so hard on yourself.

200
00:13:29.380 --> 00:13:31.490
Who could have guessed your
own brother would betray you?

201
00:13:31.580 --> 00:13:34.260
Well. I did have a front row seat
when your sister lied to you.

202
00:13:34.330 --> 00:13:37.450
Yeah. well.
she's fickle. that one.

203
00:13:37.500 --> 00:13:39.470
And you say you have no
idea of her whereabouts?

204
00:13:39.550 --> 00:13:41.800
That's the thing
with younger siblings.

205
00:13:41.890 --> 00:13:44.390
You just... never
know what they're going to do.

206
00:13:47.840 --> 00:13:50.650
Drink?

207
00:13:53.600 --> 00:13:54.850
Thanks.

208
00:13:54.930 --> 00:13:56.850
This is weird.

209
00:13:56.940 --> 00:13:58.470
Klaus has hybrids stalking me.

210
00:13:58.520 --> 00:14:00.910
and now. you're just sitting
in our kitchen.

211
00:14:00.970 --> 00:14:02.320
Look. maybe I should go.

212
00:14:02.410 --> 00:14:04.280
No. stay. You're not
doing anything.

213
00:14:04.330 --> 00:14:07.860
Unless you have to. you know.
check in with your hybrid master.

214
00:14:07.950 --> 00:14:10.120
It's not like that. Elena.

215
00:14:10.170 --> 00:14:11.650
Tell me. Tyler...

216
00:14:11.700 --> 00:14:13.150
What is the difference.

217
00:14:13.200 --> 00:14:16.140
Between being sired
and being compelled?

218
00:14:18.090 --> 00:14:20.790
Compulsion...
That's just mind control.

219
00:14:20.840 --> 00:14:22.980
like hypnosis.

220
00:14:23.050 --> 00:14:26.430
And being sired is...

221
00:14:26.500 --> 00:14:28.120
It's like faith.

222
00:14:28.180 --> 00:14:31.040
You do something because you
believe it's the right thing.

223
00:14:31.100 --> 00:14:34.810
So. you believe that serving
Klaus is the right thing.

224
00:14:34.860 --> 00:14:36.780
I don't serve him.

225
00:14:36.840 --> 00:14:40.450
Klaus released me from a curse
that was ruining my life.

226
00:14:40.510 --> 00:14:41.810
I owe him for that.

227
00:14:41.870 --> 00:14:44.480
What if he asked you to...

228
00:14:44.530 --> 00:14:46.950
Jump off a bridge?

229
00:14:47.020 --> 00:14:49.190
He wouldn't.
And even if he did.

230
00:14:49.240 --> 00:14:50.870
I'd be fine. I'm a hybrid.

231
00:14:50.960 --> 00:14:53.240
Ok. So what if he asked you
to rip your own heart out?

232
00:14:53.330 --> 00:14:56.080
Again. he wouldn't.
What if he did?

233
00:14:56.160 --> 00:14:58.750
I don't know.
Then I'd rip out my heart.

234
00:15:00.550 --> 00:15:02.720
You guys sound like Caroline.

235
00:15:02.800 --> 00:15:05.300
getting all freaked out over
something you don't understand.

236
00:15:05.370 --> 00:15:07.540
You're right. Tyler.
I don't understand.

237
00:15:07.590 --> 00:15:09.480
Klaus has terrorized
every single one of us.

238
00:15:09.540 --> 00:15:11.310
and you're just
blindly loyal to him.

239
00:15:11.380 --> 00:15:14.100
You're overthinking it.

240
00:15:14.180 --> 00:15:16.420
I can still make
my own decisions.

241
00:15:25.990 --> 00:15:27.910
Cheers. mate.

242
00:15:27.990 --> 00:15:30.700
Down the hatch.

243
00:15:32.920 --> 00:15:35.370
You know. we've actually got
a lot in common. you and I.

244
00:15:35.420 --> 00:15:36.920
- Really?
- Heh.

245
00:15:37.000 --> 00:15:39.590
Well. yeah. Maybe we can...

246
00:15:39.670 --> 00:15:43.090
Bond over our mutual
loathing of my brother.

247
00:15:43.180 --> 00:15:45.260
Why are you so mad at him?

248
00:15:45.350 --> 00:15:47.850
He stole something?

249
00:15:47.910 --> 00:15:50.020
My family. The Originals.

250
00:15:50.080 --> 00:15:52.180
I had them daggered.
boxed up.

251
00:15:52.250 --> 00:15:54.020
awaiting the day
when I saw fit to wake them.

252
00:15:54.090 --> 00:15:56.520
And he went in
and pinched the bloody lot.

253
00:15:56.590 --> 00:15:58.860
Of course he did.

254
00:15:58.930 --> 00:16:03.030
Ah. such a buzz kill.
my baby bro.

255
00:16:03.100 --> 00:16:05.250
Well. I'd love to find him.

256
00:16:05.320 --> 00:16:07.230
Just the trouble is

257
00:16:07.280 --> 00:16:10.150
I sure as hell
don't work for you.

258
00:16:12.490 --> 00:16:14.190
You know. your drink
stinks of vervain.

259
00:16:14.260 --> 00:16:15.910
so I can't compel you.

260
00:16:15.960 --> 00:16:17.390
There'd be no point
in killing you.

261
00:16:17.460 --> 00:16:18.960
because you're actually
the one with the most hope

262
00:16:19.050 --> 00:16:20.970
of getting me what I need.
And yet. it would seem

263
00:16:21.050 --> 00:16:23.880
a demonstration is in order.

264
00:16:23.950 --> 00:16:27.790
Perhaps I wasn't clear enough
when I told you to find Stefan.

265
00:16:27.840 --> 00:16:29.120
Oh. well.

266
00:16:29.170 --> 00:16:32.690
It seems you people respond
best to displays of violence.

267
00:16:32.760 --> 00:16:36.930
Why don't you take this
as an example of my reach?

268
00:16:40.150 --> 00:16:41.600
There he is.

269
00:16:41.650 --> 00:16:43.900
So. that thing
I told you to do.

270
00:16:43.970 --> 00:16:46.970
Why don't you go ahead
and get on with it?

271
00:16:53.250 --> 00:16:55.910
- What was that about?
- It was nothing.

272
00:16:58.500 --> 00:16:59.790
I got to go.

273
00:16:59.840 --> 00:17:01.700
Um. thanks for the food offer.

274
00:17:01.790 --> 00:17:03.870
but next time...

275
00:17:03.960 --> 00:17:06.710
Ahem.

276
00:17:12.300 --> 00:17:14.880
Well. that was illuminating.

277
00:17:14.970 --> 00:17:17.350
So. Tyler Lockwood is.

278
00:17:17.440 --> 00:17:19.140
A lunatic who has
access to our house.

279
00:17:19.190 --> 00:17:25.310
I mean. this whole
sire bond thing is wild.

280
00:17:25.360 --> 00:17:27.180
I don't even think
Tyler's fully aware of.

281
00:17:27.230 --> 00:17:29.310
What little reason lies
behind what he's saying.

282
00:17:29.370 --> 00:17:30.900
It's... it's
his weird cult logic.

283
00:17:30.980 --> 00:17:35.290
Well. great. That's a wonderful
influence for you. Jer.

284
00:17:35.350 --> 00:17:38.710
Jeremy?

285
00:17:38.790 --> 00:17:41.690
That's his ring.

286
00:17:42.800 --> 00:17:44.700
Where'd he go?

287
00:17:46.370 --> 00:17:48.870
Jeremy?

288
00:17:48.920 --> 00:17:50.700
What is he doing?

289
00:17:54.310 --> 00:17:56.310
Oh. my god. Jeremy!

290
00:17:56.380 --> 00:17:59.090
Jeremy! Jeremy. move!

291
00:18:23.970 --> 00:18:26.360
There I go again.
bumping into people.

292
00:18:32.370 --> 00:18:34.320
That's Klaus' hybrid.

293
00:18:35.570 --> 00:18:38.200
He's going to be all right.
Are you ok?

294
00:18:38.270 --> 00:18:39.440
I don't understand.

295
00:18:39.490 --> 00:18:41.120
Who was that on
the phone earlier?

296
00:18:42.330 --> 00:18:43.580
It was Klaus.

297
00:18:43.630 --> 00:18:46.500
You were compelled. Jeremy.

298
00:18:46.580 --> 00:18:48.610
We've got to get him inside.
Help me.

299
00:18:51.670 --> 00:18:53.590
Compel the men
to open up this wall.

300
00:18:53.640 --> 00:18:55.590
We need sun.

301
00:18:55.640 --> 00:18:57.620
I want a fortress.
not a dungeon.

302
00:18:57.670 --> 00:19:01.180
There he is. Man of the hour.

303
00:19:01.260 --> 00:19:02.930
So everything went ok?

304
00:19:02.980 --> 00:19:06.100
Tony ran down Alaric instead
of Jeremy. but apples. oranges.

305
00:19:06.150 --> 00:19:07.820
Message learns the same.

306
00:19:07.900 --> 00:19:09.990
You said you were sending
them a warning.

307
00:19:10.070 --> 00:19:11.440
And I did... an effective one.

308
00:19:11.500 --> 00:19:12.940
Elena's family suffers.

309
00:19:12.990 --> 00:19:15.160
she's motivated
to get me what I want.

310
00:19:15.240 --> 00:19:18.490
I didn't think that we'd actually
have to kill anyone.

311
00:19:20.950 --> 00:19:22.950
Tyler. mate.

312
00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:25.330
What you're feeling is the remnant
of a guilty conscience.

313
00:19:25.420 --> 00:19:27.670
I need you to get over it. ok?

314
00:19:27.750 --> 00:19:29.150
End of the day.

315
00:19:29.210 --> 00:19:31.820
human life here is
just a means to an end...

316
00:19:31.870 --> 00:19:34.590
Our means to our end.

317
00:19:34.660 --> 00:19:36.880
You'd do well to remember that.

318
00:19:44.020 --> 00:19:45.190
How is he?

319
00:19:45.250 --> 00:19:47.890
He's dead.
but he had his ring.

320
00:19:47.970 --> 00:19:51.510
Klaus' hybrid hit him.
Now we just wait.

321
00:19:51.580 --> 00:19:54.610
Jeremy. why aren't you wearing vervain

322
00:19:56.180 --> 00:19:58.180
I don't know.

323
00:19:58.230 --> 00:19:59.730
It was Tyler.

324
00:19:59.820 --> 00:20:00.970
It had to have been.

325
00:20:01.040 --> 00:20:02.970
That's why he was
hanging out with you.

326
00:20:03.040 --> 00:20:04.520
to get you off the vervain.

327
00:20:04.570 --> 00:20:05.740
Klaus is trying to
send us a message.

328
00:20:05.830 --> 00:20:07.990
He wants us to find Stefan.

329
00:20:08.040 --> 00:20:09.830
who stole his coffins of all
his dead family members.

330
00:20:09.880 --> 00:20:12.160
- Coffins?
- Yep.

331
00:20:12.210 --> 00:20:14.000
So all we have to do is
find 4 coffins.

332
00:20:14.050 --> 00:20:15.420
and voila.

333
00:20:15.500 --> 00:20:17.720
no one else on your family's
christmas list has to die.

334
00:20:17.800 --> 00:20:19.500
Wait. that's your big plan.

335
00:20:19.560 --> 00:20:21.420
to steal back 4 dead Originals.

336
00:20:21.510 --> 00:20:23.010
So this evil hybrid
doesn't kill me.

337
00:20:23.060 --> 00:20:24.340
And everyone else we know?

338
00:20:24.390 --> 00:20:25.480
- You got a better idea?
- Yeah.

339
00:20:25.540 --> 00:20:27.010
Let's get the hell out of here.

340
00:20:27.060 --> 00:20:28.210
Pack our bags and go.

341
00:20:28.260 --> 00:20:29.260
Hey. Jeremy. calm down.

342
00:20:29.350 --> 00:20:30.850
No. No. I'm not going
to calm down. Elena.

343
00:20:30.900 --> 00:20:33.690
This happens every time
no matter what we do...

344
00:20:33.740 --> 00:20:37.190
You get on my case about school and work.
Who cares.

345
00:20:37.240 --> 00:20:40.240
None of us are going to make it
out of this town alive.

346
00:20:47.400 --> 00:20:49.570
He said he wants
his family back.

347
00:20:51.620 --> 00:20:54.670
No. No. I know what you're thinking.
The answer's no.

348
00:20:54.740 --> 00:20:55.840
If we give him Rebekah...

349
00:20:55.910 --> 00:20:57.380
Yeah. then Klaus
un-daggers her.

350
00:20:57.430 --> 00:20:58.710
First thing she does
is kill you.

351
00:20:58.740 --> 00:21:01.010
Frying pan. fire.
Not an option.

352
00:21:01.080 --> 00:21:03.580
Klaus's coffins.

353
00:21:03.630 --> 00:21:05.420
How many did you say
there were?

354
00:21:07.440 --> 00:21:10.610
Elena? Hey.

355
00:21:10.690 --> 00:21:13.730
Klaus is looking for 4 coffins.
just like in your dream.

356
00:21:13.780 --> 00:21:15.390
I think it's not just stress.

357
00:21:15.440 --> 00:21:16.950
Elena. don't get involved.

358
00:21:17.030 --> 00:21:19.230
Whatever Klaus wants.
stay as far away from it as you can.

359
00:21:19.280 --> 00:21:21.620
Klaus won't let me. Bonnie...

360
00:21:21.700 --> 00:21:23.620
He tried to kill Jeremy.

361
00:21:27.020 --> 00:21:28.290
What do you want me to do?

362
00:21:28.370 --> 00:21:30.080
We need to find Stefan.

363
00:21:30.130 --> 00:21:31.790
Look. I know that
you don't think.

364
00:21:31.880 --> 00:21:33.460
That your locater spell
still works.

365
00:21:33.550 --> 00:21:35.580
but we have to at least try.

366
00:21:35.630 --> 00:21:39.670
We don't need a locater spell.

367
00:21:40.840 --> 00:21:43.170
Bonnie said this place
lost all its mojo.

368
00:21:43.260 --> 00:21:46.340
The dead witches were angry at her
for bringing Jeremy back to life.

369
00:21:46.430 --> 00:21:48.130
I guess now they have something
they want her to know.

370
00:21:48.180 --> 00:21:51.180
That's why I hate witches.
So fickle.

371
00:21:51.260 --> 00:21:53.000
passive-aggressive.

372
00:21:53.070 --> 00:21:54.980
Stefan?

373
00:21:55.070 --> 00:21:57.150
Come on. Stef.
Olly olly oxen free.

374
00:22:01.640 --> 00:22:03.790
Really.

375
00:22:03.860 --> 00:22:04.910
What?

376
00:22:04.980 --> 00:22:06.980
The witchy spirits
aren't a big fan.

377
00:22:07.030 --> 00:22:10.330
and they used their juju
to screw with my daylight ring.

378
00:22:10.420 --> 00:22:12.120
- Then wait outside.
- Elena...

379
00:22:12.170 --> 00:22:15.040
I'm not leaving until
I know if he's here.

380
00:22:24.850 --> 00:22:26.680
Stefan?

381
00:22:28.680 --> 00:22:30.770
Go away.

382
00:22:34.490 --> 00:22:36.170
You shouldn't be here. Elena.

383
00:22:36.230 --> 00:22:37.860
Stefan. I need your help.

384
00:22:37.940 --> 00:22:39.301
Bonnie said that
you would be here.

385
00:22:39.340 --> 00:22:41.780
Well. Bonnie sucks
at keeping secrets.

386
00:22:41.850 --> 00:22:44.200
Listen. you need to give
Klaus his family back.

387
00:22:44.280 --> 00:22:46.700
Oh. really

388
00:22:46.790 --> 00:22:50.350
Klaus compelled Jeremy to stand
in front of a speeding car.

389
00:22:52.310 --> 00:22:54.060
Don't you get it?

390
00:22:54.130 --> 00:22:56.830
Stefan. he's not going to stop
until he gets what he wants...

391
00:22:56.880 --> 00:22:58.850
Elena. stop talking.

392
00:22:58.910 --> 00:23:00.420
I'm not giving Klaus anything.

393
00:23:00.500 --> 00:23:03.840
Are you listening to me?

394
00:23:03.890 --> 00:23:05.890
He's going to kill Jeremy.

395
00:23:07.990 --> 00:23:10.480
Not really my problem.

396
00:23:16.350 --> 00:23:18.220
You can go to hell.

397
00:23:26.590 --> 00:23:28.260
That didn't go over well.

398
00:23:28.310 --> 00:23:29.680
Don't even start. Damon.

399
00:23:29.760 --> 00:23:32.180
Let me talk to him.
You can't get in.

400
00:23:32.270 --> 00:23:34.100
The witches won't let you.

401
00:23:35.600 --> 00:23:37.190
Here.

402
00:23:37.270 --> 00:23:38.940
Take my car keys.

403
00:23:38.990 --> 00:23:40.760
You go deal with your brother.

404
00:23:40.830 --> 00:23:43.690
I'll deal with mine.

405
00:24:02.860 --> 00:24:05.670
Wow.

406
00:24:05.720 --> 00:24:07.050
That was impressive.

407
00:24:07.120 --> 00:24:09.100
But the coffins aren't here.

408
00:24:09.170 --> 00:24:11.440
so you can go away now.

409
00:24:11.510 --> 00:24:15.010
I don't care about the coffins.

410
00:24:15.080 --> 00:24:17.180
We need to talk.

411
00:24:19.280 --> 00:24:21.450
Ohh! Ow!

412
00:24:21.520 --> 00:24:23.200
Ok.

413
00:24:25.620 --> 00:24:27.320
Let's talk.

414
00:24:29.540 --> 00:24:32.440
Nothing's ever easy
with you. is it?

415
00:24:42.590 --> 00:24:45.760
That is for screwing up
my plan.

416
00:24:45.840 --> 00:24:47.441
- Ugh!
- You stopped me from killing Klaus.

417
00:24:47.510 --> 00:24:49.340
and you steal his family.
Why?

418
00:24:49.390 --> 00:24:50.680
It doesn't make sense.

419
00:24:50.730 --> 00:24:52.600
Answer me!

420
00:24:52.680 --> 00:24:54.760
Piece by piece.

421
00:24:54.850 --> 00:24:56.720
Klaus took everything from me.

422
00:24:56.770 --> 00:24:58.520
I'm doing the same to him.

423
00:24:58.570 --> 00:24:59.740
But I had him. Stefan!

424
00:24:59.820 --> 00:25:01.270
Aah!

425
00:25:01.360 --> 00:25:04.570
- Why'd you screw it up?
- I did it to save you!

426
00:25:04.660 --> 00:25:06.740
What?

427
00:25:10.230 --> 00:25:12.500
No. No way.

428
00:25:13.950 --> 00:25:15.370
You didn't do this for me.

429
00:25:15.420 --> 00:25:17.700
He was one step ahead of us.

430
00:25:17.760 --> 00:25:20.260
If Klaus died. his hybrids
would have killed you.

431
00:25:20.340 --> 00:25:22.340
When are you going to get
it through your head?

432
00:25:22.410 --> 00:25:24.590
Ohh!

433
00:25:24.680 --> 00:25:26.680
Stop saving me.

434
00:25:34.690 --> 00:25:36.020
Don't do it. Jeremy.

435
00:25:36.090 --> 00:25:39.110
Why not?
You stab my back. I stab yours.

436
00:25:39.190 --> 00:25:41.390
I didn't stab you in the back.

437
00:25:41.450 --> 00:25:42.860
Is that why you wanted
to hang out.

438
00:25:42.930 --> 00:25:44.230
to get me off the vervain?

439
00:25:44.280 --> 00:25:46.450
Klaus asked me to.
I never thought he would try to kill you.

440
00:25:46.530 --> 00:25:49.370
It's Klaus. Tyler.
What did you think was going to happen?

441
00:25:49.440 --> 00:25:50.700
He doesn't care about you.

442
00:25:50.770 --> 00:25:53.210
All he wants is to get
his family back.

443
00:25:53.270 --> 00:25:55.610
What the hell!

444
00:25:55.660 --> 00:25:58.950
Whenever Klaus wants something.
someone ends up dead.

445
00:25:59.000 --> 00:26:02.780
You think about that next time before
you blindly do whatever he says.

446
00:26:08.220 --> 00:26:11.410
Jer. you should get home.
Stay inside.

447
00:26:11.480 --> 00:26:15.730
Klaus isn't going to stop until
he gets all those coffins back.

448
00:26:17.480 --> 00:26:19.820
He's not done with you.

449
00:26:28.580 --> 00:26:31.310
Ric. Hey.
When did you return to the living?

450
00:26:31.360 --> 00:26:34.200
Oh. just a few minutes ago.
How's Jeremy?

451
00:26:34.280 --> 00:26:36.200
Hating me.

452
00:26:36.280 --> 00:26:37.700
Hating life.
Hating the life that.

453
00:26:37.790 --> 00:26:39.151
We can't even have
a family dinner.

454
00:26:39.170 --> 00:26:41.500
Without somebody dying
before dessert. Are you ok?

455
00:26:43.760 --> 00:26:45.040
Oh. my god. Ugh.

456
00:26:45.130 --> 00:26:47.430
Something's wrong. The ring.

457
00:26:47.490 --> 00:26:49.500
Ohh. Ric. Hey.

458
00:26:49.550 --> 00:26:51.850
What happened?

459
00:26:51.930 --> 00:26:55.270
He got hit by a car.
and he's coughing up blood.

460
00:26:55.340 --> 00:26:57.140
Get his vitals.

461
00:26:57.190 --> 00:26:58.690
Pulse thready and weak.

462
00:26:58.770 --> 00:27:00.640
Looks like internal bleeding.
We got to get him out of here.

463
00:27:00.690 --> 00:27:03.640
Let's move.
Let's not and say we did.

464
00:27:03.690 --> 00:27:05.530
Why don't you two meet us
at the hospital?

465
00:27:06.730 --> 00:27:08.350
What?

466
00:27:08.400 --> 00:27:09.980
No. No. no. no. Wait.

467
00:27:10.030 --> 00:27:11.990
No. wait. You have to help him.

468
00:27:12.040 --> 00:27:13.870
What are you doing?

469
00:27:13.960 --> 00:27:15.710
You can still save
his life. Elena.

470
00:27:15.790 --> 00:27:17.540
Here. Take my blood.

471
00:27:17.630 --> 00:27:19.210
But...

472
00:27:21.210 --> 00:27:23.810
I can't get in.

473
00:27:23.880 --> 00:27:25.370
You're going to have
to invite me.

474
00:27:25.420 --> 00:27:27.200
No. Why are you doing this?

475
00:27:27.250 --> 00:27:28.590
Klaus asked for his family.

476
00:27:28.670 --> 00:27:29.970
You didn't deliver.

477
00:27:30.040 --> 00:27:31.810
Ric!

478
00:27:31.870 --> 00:27:34.040
Oh. my god. Ric.
I'm right here.

479
00:27:34.090 --> 00:27:35.560
Hey. Hey. look.

480
00:27:36.810 --> 00:27:38.480
I would invite me in. Elena.

481
00:27:47.870 --> 00:27:50.660
Jeremy. He's not dead yet.

482
00:27:54.000 --> 00:27:55.500
Where are you going?

483
00:28:04.670 --> 00:28:06.170
What are you doing?

484
00:28:14.220 --> 00:28:16.680
Now he's dead.

485
00:28:22.810 --> 00:28:25.430
We've got to get Alaric
to the hospital. now.

486
00:28:38.240 --> 00:28:39.520
You know what
I can't figure out?

487
00:28:39.560 --> 00:28:42.200
Why save me?

488
00:28:42.280 --> 00:28:45.070
Was it brotherly love.
guilty conscience.

489
00:28:45.150 --> 00:28:46.780
Is the switch on.
is the switch off?

490
00:28:46.850 --> 00:28:48.400
Do you have somewhere
you need to be. Damon?

491
00:28:48.490 --> 00:28:50.320
Ah. deflection.

492
00:28:50.370 --> 00:28:52.460
That's not going to work on me.
I invented that.

493
00:28:52.520 --> 00:28:55.540
We're done.
Can't you just go away?

494
00:28:55.630 --> 00:28:56.860
Not until you tell me
why you saved me.

495
00:28:56.910 --> 00:28:57.960
You owe me that.

496
00:28:58.030 --> 00:28:59.550
I don't owe you anything.

497
00:28:59.630 --> 00:29:02.080
Fine.

498
00:29:02.170 --> 00:29:03.420
Next question.

499
00:29:03.500 --> 00:29:04.850
why did you steal the coffins?

500
00:29:04.920 --> 00:29:07.200
Because Klaus's family is one
weakness I can use against him.

501
00:29:07.260 --> 00:29:08.640
Use against him to do what?

502
00:29:08.710 --> 00:29:10.660
You're not going to kill him.
You know how I know this?

503
00:29:10.730 --> 00:29:12.390
'Cause there was only
one way to kill him.

504
00:29:12.480 --> 00:29:13.930
and you blew that to save me.

505
00:29:14.000 --> 00:29:15.150
You're wrong. Damon.

506
00:29:15.210 --> 00:29:17.830
Klaus doesn't get
to just live forever.

507
00:29:17.900 --> 00:29:20.870
There's another way.
There has to be.

508
00:29:20.940 --> 00:29:24.610
Fair enough.

509
00:29:24.670 --> 00:29:25.950
Whatever you're doing.
I want in.

510
00:29:26.020 --> 00:29:27.610
I don't need your help.

511
00:29:27.690 --> 00:29:29.110
Really?
Last time I checked.

512
00:29:29.180 --> 00:29:30.260
you were hiding out
in a haunted house.

513
00:29:30.330 --> 00:29:31.900
I'm in this alone. Damon.

514
00:29:31.950 --> 00:29:34.550
You go after Klaus. you're going
to have to be cutthroat and devious.

515
00:29:34.620 --> 00:29:36.830
I'm so much better
at that than you.

516
00:29:38.290 --> 00:29:40.920
Come on. brother.

517
00:29:41.010 --> 00:29:42.170
What do you say?

518
00:29:42.240 --> 00:29:44.120
If you're going to
keep saving my life.

519
00:29:44.240 --> 00:29:46.510
at least make it
for a good reason.

520
00:29:46.580 --> 00:29:50.250
You want in. huh?

521
00:29:50.300 --> 00:29:53.000
Ok. But it's just me and you.

522
00:29:53.070 --> 00:29:55.090
- Elena stays out of it.
- Deal.

523
00:29:55.140 --> 00:29:56.800
Follow me.

524
00:29:56.890 --> 00:30:00.190
Wait. I'm not so...
Welcome in there.

525
00:30:00.260 --> 00:30:03.390
Don't you worry. Damon.
We all want the same thing.

526
00:30:07.870 --> 00:30:10.150
Have a look.

527
00:30:10.230 --> 00:30:11.650
What?

528
00:30:11.740 --> 00:30:13.490
Klaus is allergic to dust?

529
00:30:13.550 --> 00:30:15.840
Mmm. Look again.

530
00:30:19.710 --> 00:30:22.330
Witch spirits hate Klaus
as much as we do.

531
00:30:22.410 --> 00:30:24.280
They're using their powers
to hide the coffins.

532
00:30:24.330 --> 00:30:26.080
So if he comes in the house...

533
00:30:26.130 --> 00:30:29.050
He won't be able to find them.

534
00:30:37.060 --> 00:30:40.460
Mr. Saltzman. What are you doing up?
You should be resting.

535
00:30:40.520 --> 00:30:44.820
Uh. I'm more of a
walk-it-off kind of guy.

536
00:30:44.900 --> 00:30:47.300
Ahem. Do I need
to sign something?

537
00:30:47.370 --> 00:30:50.810
Internal hemorrhaging. 3 broken
ribs. and a severe concussion.

538
00:30:50.860 --> 00:30:53.330
I have no idea how you're
on your feet right now.

539
00:30:53.410 --> 00:30:54.731
but I need to run
some more tests.

540
00:30:54.750 --> 00:30:56.810
Actually. I have someplace
I need to be.

541
00:30:56.860 --> 00:30:59.150
But thank you. Doctor...

542
00:30:59.200 --> 00:31:02.290
Fell.

543
00:31:02.340 --> 00:31:05.790
But the patience who follow my
advice get to call me Meredith.

544
00:31:07.180 --> 00:31:12.460
Well. I appreciate your help.
Dr. Fell.

545
00:31:13.850 --> 00:31:15.680
Mr. Saltzman...

546
00:31:15.770 --> 00:31:19.470
What is your secret?

547
00:31:19.520 --> 00:31:21.810
Guardian angel. or did you sell
your soul to the devil?

548
00:31:25.040 --> 00:31:26.860
Little of both.

549
00:31:36.570 --> 00:31:38.070
Thank you for coming.

550
00:31:38.160 --> 00:31:42.490
I trust you have news
of Stefan.

551
00:31:42.540 --> 00:31:44.660
I couldn't find him.

552
00:31:46.880 --> 00:31:49.080
But I have something else.

553
00:31:55.660 --> 00:31:57.890
My poor sister.

554
00:31:59.040 --> 00:32:01.190
I can't turn my back
on her for a moment.

555
00:32:01.260 --> 00:32:03.850
You have Rebekah.

556
00:32:03.900 --> 00:32:05.180
A deal is a deal.

557
00:32:05.230 --> 00:32:07.400
The life of my sister
in exchange for your brother?

558
00:32:07.490 --> 00:32:09.270
Yeah. I'd say that's a bargain.

559
00:32:09.350 --> 00:32:12.190
Consider him spared.

560
00:32:12.240 --> 00:32:14.990
You should know.

561
00:32:15.060 --> 00:32:17.090
I was the one
that daggered her.

562
00:32:17.160 --> 00:32:19.210
When she wakes.
she'll come after me.

563
00:32:19.280 --> 00:32:22.570
I can control Rebekah.

564
00:32:22.620 --> 00:32:25.900
Besides. I still need
your help finding Stefan.

565
00:32:25.950 --> 00:32:29.120
I told you.
I don't know where he is.

566
00:32:32.290 --> 00:32:33.630
You're lying.

567
00:32:33.710 --> 00:32:35.580
Fortunately.

568
00:32:35.630 --> 00:32:37.130
you have no shortage
of loved ones.

569
00:32:37.220 --> 00:32:38.600
If I don't find my family.

570
00:32:38.680 --> 00:32:39.970
the question you should
be asking yourself is.

571
00:32:40.030 --> 00:32:42.720
who's going to die next?
Bonnie? Caroline?

572
00:32:42.770 --> 00:32:44.990
Damon?

573
00:32:48.930 --> 00:32:51.980
It's only a matter of time before
Stefan gives me what I want.

574
00:32:52.060 --> 00:32:54.930
He doesn't care
about me any more.

575
00:32:55.000 --> 00:32:56.980
You made sure of that.

576
00:32:57.070 --> 00:32:59.070
You turned him into a monster.

577
00:33:01.820 --> 00:33:03.370
Now he's your problem.

578
00:33:06.490 --> 00:33:09.050
And just so you know.

579
00:33:09.110 --> 00:33:12.420
I'm not the only one
Rebekah wants dead.

580
00:33:12.470 --> 00:33:16.420
She knows what you did
to your mother.

581
00:33:16.470 --> 00:33:18.140
She knows that you killed her.

582
00:33:26.680 --> 00:33:29.250
You can let yourself out.

583
00:33:39.180 --> 00:33:40.810
So the ring brought you
back to life.

584
00:33:40.880 --> 00:33:43.710
but it didn't heal you.
Does that mean it's broken?

585
00:33:43.760 --> 00:33:45.210
I don't know.

586
00:33:45.260 --> 00:33:47.180
It's never happened
like that before.

587
00:33:47.230 --> 00:33:49.520
I guess I have
Damon's blood to thank.

588
00:33:49.570 --> 00:33:51.400
For the fact that
I'm still walking.

589
00:33:51.490 --> 00:33:53.520
He said to say
you owe him a drink.

590
00:33:53.570 --> 00:33:55.190
That's funny.

591
00:33:55.240 --> 00:33:57.190
I'd rather have head trauma.

592
00:33:57.240 --> 00:33:59.060
Hey. Jeremy...

593
00:34:00.500 --> 00:34:01.630
You ok?

594
00:34:01.700 --> 00:34:03.400
Why wouldn't I be?

595
00:34:03.470 --> 00:34:05.670
I shot a hybrid in the back

596
00:34:05.740 --> 00:34:07.240
and chopped his head off
with a meat cleaver.

597
00:34:07.300 --> 00:34:09.600
What.

598
00:34:09.670 --> 00:34:13.610
You can talk to me about this stuff.
You know that. right?

599
00:34:13.680 --> 00:34:15.910
What could you tell me
that I don't already know?

600
00:34:17.450 --> 00:34:19.380
This is the way things are.

601
00:34:19.450 --> 00:34:23.440
It sucks. but I just got
to get used to it.

602
00:34:37.620 --> 00:34:39.450
Did you get rid of him?

603
00:34:39.540 --> 00:34:41.650
Yeah.
Tony the headless hybrid's.

604
00:34:41.740 --> 00:34:43.410
Now at the bottom
of Steven's quarry.

605
00:34:43.460 --> 00:34:44.740
What about Alaric?

606
00:34:44.790 --> 00:34:46.120
Took care of him. too.

607
00:34:46.210 --> 00:34:48.610
He'll be fine.

608
00:34:48.660 --> 00:34:49.940
How are you?

609
00:34:50.000 --> 00:34:52.210
I think I got most of the
blood off the porch.

610
00:34:52.280 --> 00:34:54.550
Elena.

611
00:34:54.620 --> 00:34:57.090
Look at me.

612
00:35:01.910 --> 00:35:04.030
It's going to be ok.

613
00:35:05.680 --> 00:35:07.980
I have to tell you something.

614
00:35:10.350 --> 00:35:12.420
I made a deal with Klaus.

615
00:35:12.490 --> 00:35:13.770
I gave him Rebekah.

616
00:35:13.820 --> 00:35:15.100
What?

617
00:35:15.150 --> 00:35:17.860
No. no. No.
You did not do that.

618
00:35:17.920 --> 00:35:19.470
She's going to come here
and try and kill you.

619
00:35:19.530 --> 00:35:22.190
No. she won't.
Klaus won't let her because he needs me.

620
00:35:22.280 --> 00:35:23.500
And suddenly. you trust him?

621
00:35:23.580 --> 00:35:24.910
No. I don't trust him.

622
00:35:24.980 --> 00:35:27.020
But what other choice
do I have?

623
00:35:27.080 --> 00:35:29.820
I don't trust Stefan.

624
00:35:29.870 --> 00:35:32.840
Do you think he's just going
to give up the coffins?

625
00:35:34.820 --> 00:35:36.820
My brother's...

626
00:35:36.880 --> 00:35:38.930
Sort of running
his own show right now.

627
00:35:38.990 --> 00:35:41.660
Yeah. My brother just
chopped off someone's head.

628
00:35:42.830 --> 00:35:46.470
It's not right.

629
00:35:46.520 --> 00:35:49.440
It's not fair.
He's 16 years old.

630
00:35:49.510 --> 00:35:51.670
He shouldn't have
to live like this.

631
00:35:53.730 --> 00:35:55.680
Elena...

632
00:35:55.730 --> 00:35:58.680
There has to be another way.

633
00:35:58.730 --> 00:36:00.010
I have to fix it.

634
00:36:00.070 --> 00:36:01.700
We will.

635
00:36:01.780 --> 00:36:03.490
Hey.

636
00:36:03.540 --> 00:36:06.040
Hey.

637
00:36:06.120 --> 00:36:08.790
Hey.

638
00:36:08.860 --> 00:36:11.690
We will.

639
00:36:11.740 --> 00:36:13.910
Ok?

640
00:36:22.870 --> 00:36:24.590
Here we are. Rebekah.

641
00:36:24.670 --> 00:36:27.930
Home. sweet home.

642
00:36:28.010 --> 00:36:30.680
Only took 1.000 years.

643
00:36:30.750 --> 00:36:32.760
And to think.

644
00:36:32.850 --> 00:36:36.640
I was counting on you
being here with me.

645
00:36:36.700 --> 00:36:39.440
But that's all ruined now.
isn't it?

646
00:36:52.900 --> 00:36:55.900
I'm so sorry.

647
00:36:59.260 --> 00:37:01.110
Sister.

648
00:37:04.930 --> 00:37:07.300
We'll meet again one day.

649
00:37:19.700 --> 00:37:22.280
Hey. Can we talk?

650
00:37:22.370 --> 00:37:25.050
What did I do now?

651
00:37:25.120 --> 00:37:28.570
I've been thinking
about what you said earlier.

652
00:37:28.620 --> 00:37:30.540
about how we should
pack up and go.

653
00:37:30.610 --> 00:37:32.210
Elena. I didn't mean
any of that.

654
00:37:32.270 --> 00:37:33.460
But you were right.

655
00:37:33.540 --> 00:37:37.630
You shouldn't have
to give up a normal life.

656
00:37:37.710 --> 00:37:38.710
Just because of me.

657
00:37:38.780 --> 00:37:40.380
What's going on?

658
00:37:40.450 --> 00:37:42.770
Your sister thinks we should
have another one of our talks.

659
00:37:48.810 --> 00:37:51.680
Here's the thing. Jeremy.

660
00:37:51.760 --> 00:37:54.680
You're going to go out of
town for a little while.

661
00:37:55.850 --> 00:37:57.300
A long while.

662
00:37:57.370 --> 00:38:00.800
You're going to stay with some
nice family friends in Denver.

663
00:38:00.850 --> 00:38:04.490
You're going to be in a new
school and meet new girls...

664
00:38:04.570 --> 00:38:06.270
Living girls.

665
00:38:06.330 --> 00:38:08.490
You're going to drink a few beers.
take an art class.

666
00:38:08.580 --> 00:38:09.940
You can do whatever you want.

667
00:38:10.000 --> 00:38:13.630
Tell him he's going to
leave mystic falls behind

668
00:38:13.700 --> 00:38:16.670
and never think twice about it.

669
00:38:23.960 --> 00:38:25.630
You're going to leave
mystic falls behind

670
00:38:25.690 --> 00:38:27.550
and never think twice about it.

671
00:38:31.300 --> 00:38:33.520
You're going to have
a better life. Jeremy.

672
00:38:51.520 --> 00:38:54.020
This is the one I dreamed of.

673
00:38:54.870 --> 00:38:56.830
Don't bother. It won't open.

674
00:38:56.880 --> 00:38:58.360
What do you mean.
is it locked?

675
00:38:58.410 --> 00:39:01.160
Nope. It just won't open.
I've tried everything...

676
00:39:01.230 --> 00:39:03.360
Blow torch. ax. crowbar.

677
00:39:03.420 --> 00:39:04.870
I can't even scratch
the finish.

678
00:39:04.920 --> 00:39:06.790
That means it's closed
with a spell.

679
00:39:06.850 --> 00:39:09.020
You mean whatever's in there
should probably stay in there.

680
00:39:09.090 --> 00:39:11.810
You said you wanted
to make him suffer.

681
00:39:11.870 --> 00:39:14.580
The witches led me here
for a reason.

682
00:39:14.640 --> 00:39:17.430
I think whatever's inside
this coffin is our answer.

683
00:39:23.520 --> 00:39:26.550
I feel like
a horrible person.

684
00:39:26.610 --> 00:39:28.990
You just saved his life. Elena.

685
00:39:29.060 --> 00:39:31.160
Take it from me...
Estranged is bad.

686
00:39:31.230 --> 00:39:32.730
Dead is worse.

687
00:39:32.780 --> 00:39:34.830
Just can't stop thinking
about what happened.

688
00:39:34.900 --> 00:39:37.000
The last time I asked
you to compel him.

689
00:39:37.070 --> 00:39:39.000
He found out.
and he got over it.

690
00:39:39.070 --> 00:39:41.670
Again. not dead. Elena.

691
00:39:44.760 --> 00:39:47.340
He's so lucky to have
you for a sister.

692
00:39:51.050 --> 00:39:52.300
Thank you.

693
00:39:52.360 --> 00:39:53.630
No problem.

694
00:39:53.720 --> 00:39:56.630
Not just for this. Damon.
For everything.

695
00:39:56.700 --> 00:40:00.540
I don't know what I would
do if you weren't here.

696
00:40:08.880 --> 00:40:11.480
You should know this. Elena.

697
00:40:11.570 --> 00:40:14.400
Stefan didn't screw us over.

698
00:40:14.450 --> 00:40:16.050
He screwed us over.
but he had a good reason.

699
00:40:16.120 --> 00:40:18.270
What?

700
00:40:18.320 --> 00:40:21.580
He saved Klaus to save me.

701
00:40:23.380 --> 00:40:25.880
Then he stole
the coffins to get even.

702
00:40:25.950 --> 00:40:29.380
Damon. if he did it
to protect you. then...

703
00:40:29.450 --> 00:40:30.890
Why would he even do that?
I mean...

704
00:40:30.950 --> 00:40:33.640
Oh. what does it even mean?

705
00:40:33.720 --> 00:40:35.390
What does it mean?

706
00:40:35.460 --> 00:40:37.680
It means I'm an idiot.

707
00:40:37.760 --> 00:40:39.910
'Cause I thought for one second

708
00:40:39.980 --> 00:40:42.060
that I wouldn't have to
feel guilty any more.

709
00:40:42.130 --> 00:40:44.980
What are you talking about.
guilty for what?

710
00:40:48.350 --> 00:40:51.190
For wanting what I want.

711
00:40:55.610 --> 00:40:57.030
Damon...

712
00:40:57.110 --> 00:40:59.780
No. I know.
Believe me. I get it.

713
00:40:59.830 --> 00:41:03.990
My brother's girl and all.

714
00:41:13.060 --> 00:41:15.600
No. No. You know what?

715
00:41:15.660 --> 00:41:17.300
If I'm going to feel
guilty about something.

716
00:41:17.350 --> 00:41:19.770
I'm going to feel guilty
about this.

717
00:41:44.910 --> 00:41:47.629
Good night.

717
00:41:48.305 --> 00:42:48.297
